   :correct: a
   :random:
   :feedback_a: Yes, one bit can represent two different values
   :feedback_b: No, two bits can represent four different values - you only have to represent two values
   :feedback_c: No, four bits can represent 16 different values - you only have to represent two values
   :feedback_d: It is possible to determine how many bits you need to represent two different values

   Imagine you have been hired to write a program for Very Simple Car Rental. The company only carries
   two colors of car - black and white. How many bits will you need to represent the color of the car requested by the customer?